title.narrative: CHILD PROTECTION IN EMERGENCIES

description.narrative: By 2021, L3, L2 and other COs directly or indirectly affected by emergencies/armed conflicts in WCAR will have received response support (technical assistance, resources and advocacy) and other selected COs in WCAR will have received technical support for preparedness., which contributes to Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every Child is protected from Violence, Exploitation and Harmful Practices.

title.narrative: By 2021, L3, L2 and other COs directly or indirectly affected by emergencies/armed conflicts in WCAR will have received responsesupport (technical assistance, resources and advocacy) and other selected COs in WCAR will have received technical support forpreparedness.

description.narrative: The ROMP 2018-2021 targets were met: 14 countries were supported to strengthen their preparedness to provide care and protection for children in emergencies and seven humanitarian-affected countries were supported to provide a timely and principled response in line with the CCCs.; This was despite a complicated environment with restrictions related to COVID-19, a volatile security environment affecting 10 countries, and the resurgence of Ebola. Increased attention was given to strengthen capacities on monitoring and reporting grave violations and advocating for children’s rights in armed conflict, and response interventions including for victims/survivors of sexual exploitation and abuse (SEA). | Status:Met | As-of Date:04/03/2022
